Matthew V. Perry
Vice President, Global Supply Chain

Matt is Vice President, Global Supply Chain for Atrium Innovations. A busy individual required to wear many different hats, Matt is responsible for ensuring reliable product supply for all of Atrium’s brands. He is also responsible for Atrium’s Contract Manufacturing Organization, as well as leads the Global Supply Chain Leadership Team.
Matt has over 22 years of Operations and Supply Chain leadership experience and has led planning, manufacturing, strategic sourcing, regulatory compliance, and distribution functions across the pharmaceutical, consumer, and medical device segments. Prior to joining Atrium, Matt’s most recent position was at Johnson and Johnson, as Vice President, Supply Chain Planning for the Global Surgery Business Unit.
In addition to work, Matt also has the honor of serving on the Board of LSNE, Inc., a leading contract development and manufacturing organization for the pharmaceutical and medical device industries.
A New Jersey resident, Matt lives in Bridgewater with Kara, his wonderful wife of nearly twenty years, and their three children. As an active member of the community, Matt has been involved with coaching youth football, baseball, and softball for over ten years. Yet another hat he wears.
Matt has a Bachelor’s of Engineering degree from Stevens Institute of Technology. He is six sigma black-belt certified and a lean manufacturing subject matter expert.











 
 



